#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:18
msgid ""
"AUTHOR: Petrus - petrus@bmail.com.au DATE: 2005-03-09 LICENSE: GNU Free "
"Documentation License.  SYNOPSIS: bmake - NetBSD's make.  DESCRIPTION: Has "
"some great extra features and is also used in pkgsrc, NetBSD's package "
"management system. Good for sysadmins, developers, or anyone who wants a "
"better and actively developed Make.  PREREQUISITES: None CHANGELOG: "
"2005-03-09 * First version.  2005-03-19 * Second version.  * Fixed newbish "
"dir shuffling * Deleted redundant sed command * jbit figured out a way to "
"cause the bootstrap test to pass"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:20
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:26
msgid ""
"The first thing to do is download "
"http://www.crufty.net/ftp/pub/sjg/bmake.tar.gz which is the source tarball "
"for bmake itself, and http://www.crufty.net/ftp/pub/sjg/mk.tar.gz which "
"contains the makefiles that bmake needs. (They contain various system rules "
"and so forth.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:32
msgid ""
"You'll need to become root in order to do this, since files need to be "
"installed to /usr/share and a few other places.  When you've downloaded "
"bmake, unpack it and cd into the bmake directory.  Bmake needs a seperate "
"OS-specific build directory, so we'll make one of those as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:39
msgid ""
"tar zxvf bmake.tar.gz mkdir -p bmake/Linux cp mk.tar.gz bmake/Linux cd "
"bmake/Linux tar zxvf mk.tar.gz ../bmake/configure --prefix=/usr"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:41
msgid "Now let's compile it:-"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:44
msgid ""
"PATH=$PWD:$PATH make -f makefile.boot bootstrap MKSRC=mk make -f "
"makefile.boot install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:51
msgid ""
"We need the first line because bmake does a test at the end of "
"bootstrapping, for which it needs to be in the PATH in order to pass.  One "
"last thing we need to do is make sure the Linux.sys.mk file is in place as "
"bmake's sys.mk, as bmake needs this in order to function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:54
msgid "cd mk cp Linux.sys.mk /usr/share/sys.mk"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:57
msgid ""
"You can test this by reinstalling bmake using bmake itself, in order to be "
"sure that sys.mk is in place and everything works."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:59
msgid "bmake install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/bmake.txt:60
msgid "It should now be working."
msgstr ""
